[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man arrested in Crowthorne after woman's body found

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who was found with serious stab wounds at a house where a woman was discovered dead has been arrested on suspicion of murder.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police were called to an address in Ellis Road, Crowthorne, Berkshire, shortly before 23:30 BST on Sunday.
The woman, aged in her 50s, was pronounced dead at the scene. Her next of kin have been informed.
The arrested man, who is in his mid-50s, is said to be in a critical condition.
Det Ch Insp Ailsa Kent, from Thames Valley Police, said: "Although we are in the early stages of conducting inquiries, this is thought to have been an isolated incident and it is believed the victim was known to the offender."
Officers are conducting inquiries in the Ellis Road area.
